<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Moria T..</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-30 04:01:14</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>In answer to the guy asking about the spawn location of the Predator.. Yes, he does spawn at the door, in the hallway.. But, the trick of this one is that he can spawn on either side of that door.. As far as his PHs, I've seen the various types of goblins all spawn there.. He's on the 18 min timer and usually end up with the PH about 5 out of 6 times.. I camped the Predator/Foreman room for 2 levels.. A very good weapon, great for any who can use it.. Wasn't lucky enough to have one drop in my time there.. Had to buy mine from someone who was logging off as I was logging on..<BR>
<BR>
Heh.. Yes, the trick is getting to this spot.. If you can work your way in, making strategic kills of the casters in the way, you can invis your way all the way up to the door.. Very hard to do and very easy to cause goblin trains that make Blackburrow gnolls envious..  <BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Moria T..</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-30 04:07:55</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Oh, yes.. The Predator and its PHs are wanderers.. They will stand still for about a minute before wandering up the hall.. Even the ones who spawn on the room side of the door will follow this path.. One cute habit they have is to open the door, look out a few times.. Finally, they will step from the room and head up the hall.. First time, they only go about half way, then return.. A few more times, getting further away each time, then they will wander all the way to the Lava zone.. But, wouldn't worry about it then.. If they make it that far, someone will snag them and they will not be returning.. <BR>
<BR>
(Heh.. now that I've pretty much given away the habits of the predator, I expect to hear about more of the shards out there!)</font></td></tr></table>
